@page "/"

<PageTitle>DigiPay — accept DigiByte on your site</PageTitle>

<div class="min-h-dvh flex flex-col bg-slate-50 dark:bg-dgb-950 text-slate-900 dark:text-white font-sans">
    <SiteNav />

    <main class="flex-1">
        @* Hero *@
        <section class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 pt-16 sm:pt-24 pb-10 sm:pb-16 text-center">
            <div class="inline-block px-3 py-1 bg-dgb-500/10 text-dgb-500 rounded-full text-xs font-semibold mb-5">
                Non-custodial · Digi-ID auth · 15-second blocks
            </div>
            <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-5xl font-bold leading-[1.1] tracking-tight max-w-4xl mx-auto">
                Accept DigiByte on your site.<br class="hidden sm:block" />
                <span class="sm:inline"> Without holding a cent of it.</span>
            </h1>
            <p class="mt-5 text-base sm:text-lg text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 max-w-2xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
                DigiPay derives a fresh address per invoice from your wallet's xpub, watches the chain,
                and notifies your server the moment a payment lands. Sign in with Digi-ID, paste an
                xpub, start accepting DGB in under a minute.
            </p>
            <div class="mt-8 flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-3 justify-center">
                @* Primary CTA swaps based on auth state — boot script sets
                   data-digipay-auth on <html> before paint, CSS hides whichever
                   variant doesn't match. *@
                <a href="/merchant/signin" data-auth-show="out"
                   class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-1.5 px-6 py-3 bg-dgb-500 hover:bg-dgb-600 text-white font-semibold rounded-xl text-sm sm:text-base no-underline transition-colors">
                    Start accepting DGB →
                </a>
                <a href="/merchant" data-auth-show="in"
                   class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-1.5 px-6 py-3 bg-dgb-500 hover:bg-dgb-600 text-white font-semibold rounded-xl text-sm sm:text-base no-underline transition-colors">
                    <Icon Name="dashboard" Class="w-4 h-4" />
                    Open dashboard →
                </a>
                <a href="/docs"
                   class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-6 py-3 bg-white dark:bg-dgb-900 border border-slate-200 dark:border-dgb-800 text-slate-900 dark:text-white font-semibold rounded-xl text-sm sm:text-base no-underline hover:bg-slate-50 dark:hover:bg-dgb-800 transition-colors">
                    How it works
                </a>
            </div>
            @* Only pitch the wallet to signed-out visitors — signed-in merchants
               already have a wallet (they signed in with Digi-ID). *@
            <p class="mt-5 text-xs text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400" data-auth-show="out">
                New to DigiByte? Grab a wallet first —
                <a href="https://dgbwallet.app" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-dgb-500 hover:underline">dgbwallet.app</a>.
            </p>
        </section>

        @* The problem DigiPay solves — contrasted with the status quo so the value prop is concrete, not abstract. *@
        <section class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-10 sm:py-14">
            <p class="text-center text-[0.6875rem] sm:text-xs font-bold tracking-widest text-dgb-500 uppercase mb-2">The problem</p>
            <h2 class="text-center text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold mb-8 sm:mb-10 tracking-tight max-w-3xl mx-auto">Why accepting crypto is usually painful</h2>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 sm:gap-5 max-w-4xl mx-auto">
                <div class="bg-white dark:bg-dgb-900 border border-red-200 dark:border-red-800/40 rounded-xl p-5 sm:p-6">
                    <div class="text-[0.6875rem] font-bold tracking-widest uppercase text-red-500 dark:text-red-400 mb-2">Without DigiPay</div>
                    <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 leading-relaxed m-0 list-disc pl-5">
                        <li>Custodial gateway holds your funds and takes a cut, plus KYC forms.</li>
                        <li>Every customer sees the same address — anyone can see your revenue.</li>
                        <li>You build the mempool watcher, webhook signer, and retry queue yourself.</li>
                        <li>Self-hosted BTCPay is powerful but heavy — needs a full node + hours to configure.</li>
                        <li>Price volatility during payment means you either eat the swing or ship reconciliation code.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-white dark:bg-dgb-900 border border-emerald-200 dark:border-emerald-800/30 rounded-xl p-5 sm:p-6">
                    <div class="text-[0.6875rem] font-bold tracking-widest uppercase text-emerald-700 dark:text-emerald-300 mb-2">With DigiPay</div>
                    <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 leading-relaxed m-0 list-disc pl-5">
                        <li>Non-custodial by design — you paste an xpub, funds flow straight to your wallet.</li>
                        <li>Fresh receive address per invoice via BIP84 derivation. Nothing links between payments.</li>
                        <li>Hosted checkout, signed webhooks, late-payment reconciliation all handled.</li>
                        <li>No node needed — DigiPay queries DigiByte explorers on your behalf.</li>
                        <li>Sign in with your wallet (Digi-ID). No password, no email, no KYC.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        @* Use cases — four concrete shapes so visitors self-identify immediately. *@
        <section class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-10 sm:py-14">
            <p class="text-center text-[0.6875rem] sm:text-xs font-bold tracking-widest text-dgb-500 uppercase mb-2">Use cases</p>
            <h2 class="text-center text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold mb-8 sm:mb-10 tracking-tight">Who this is for</h2>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-4 sm:gap-5 max-w-5xl mx-auto">
                <Feature IconName="package" Title="Online storefronts"
                    Body="Drop in a REST call from your checkout — create a session, redirect to the hosted page, listen for the session.paid webhook. Works with any stack: PHP, Node, Rust, Ruby — the API is plain HTTP." />
                <Feature IconName="gift" Title="Creators and tip jars"
                    Body="Two-line embed on your blog, Patreon, stream overlay. Static address (or rotating from xpub), optional default amount, live QR. Zero backend required." />
                <Feature IconName="code" Title="SaaS & API-driven invoicing"
                    Body="Headless: POST /v1/pay/sessions from your billing cron, attach the DGB amount to an existing invoice ID, reconcile on webhook. Late payments auto-reconcile up to 3 days." />
                <Feature IconName="users" Title="Communities & events"
                    Body="Multiple stores per account — run a tip jar, a merch shop, and an event ticket stand from one dashboard, each with its own address and webhook." />
            </div>
        </section>

        @* Features *@
        <section class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-10 sm:py-14">
            <p class="text-center text-[0.6875rem] sm:text-xs font-bold tracking-widest text-dgb-500 uppercase mb-2">What you get</p>
            <h2 class="text-center text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold mb-8 sm:mb-10 tracking-tight">Everything you need, nothing you don't</h2>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4 sm:gap-5">
                <Feature IconName="zap" Title="Hosted checkout"
                    Body="A buyer-facing page with QR + wallet deep link. Live status via SignalR — no polling your merchant UI." />
                <Feature IconName="shield" Title="Non-custodial"
                    Body="Payments go straight to your wallet. DigiPay never holds keys or funds — you don't need to trust us with anything." />
                <Feature IconName="bell" Title="Signed webhooks"
                    Body="HMAC-SHA256 POST on every state change: seen, paid, confirmed, expired, underpaid. Failed deliveries show in the dashboard with one-click replay." />
                <Feature IconName="gift" Title="Donation button"
                    Body="Zero-backend tip jar — paste a single anchor tag or a data-attribute on any page." />
                <Feature IconName="package" Title="7 KB JS embed"
                    Body="Drop-in script opens the checkout as a modal on the merchant's own page — buyer never leaves your site." />
                <Feature IconName="fingerprint" Title="Sign in with Digi-ID"
                    Body="No password, no email, no KYC. Your DigiByte wallet is your account — sign a challenge, you're in." />
            </div>
        </section>

        @* Steps *@
        <section class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-10 sm:py-14">
            <p class="text-center text-[0.6875rem] sm:text-xs font-bold tracking-widest text-dgb-500 uppercase mb-2">How it works</p>
            <h2 class="text-center text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold mb-8 sm:mb-10 tracking-tight">From zero to first payment in four steps</h2>
            <div class="grid gap-3 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
                <Step N="1" Title="Sign in with Digi-ID"
                    Body="Scan a QR with your DigiByte wallet. No account, no password — your wallet is your identity." />
                <Step N="2" Title="Paste an xpub or address"
                    Body="Account-level xpub gives you a fresh address per invoice (recommended). A single address works too for tip jars." />
                <Step N="3" Title="Create a session"
                    Body="One POST from your server returns a checkout_url. Redirect your buyer there, or open it as a modal with our 7 KB embed." />
                <Step N="4" Title="Get paid, get notified"
                    Body="Buyer pays. DigiPay detects the tx in the mempool, tracks confirmations, and POSTs a signed webhook to your server at each state change." />
            </div>
            <div class="text-center mt-8 flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-3 justify-center">
                <a href="/docs" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-5 py-2.5 bg-white dark:bg-dgb-900 border border-slate-200 dark:border-dgb-800 text-slate-900 dark:text-white font-semibold rounded-xl text-sm no-underline hover:bg-slate-50 dark:hover:bg-dgb-800 transition-colors">
                    Read the tutorial
                </a>
                <a href="/embed/demo.html" target="_blank" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-5 py-2.5 bg-white dark:bg-dgb-900 border border-slate-200 dark:border-dgb-800 text-slate-900 dark:text-white font-semibold rounded-xl text-sm no-underline hover:bg-slate-50 dark:hover:bg-dgb-800 transition-colors">
                    Live embed demo →
                </a>
            </div>
        </section>

        @* Status + Roadmap — honesty about current build so early adopters know what they're buying. *@
        <section class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-10 sm:py-14">
            <p class="text-center text-[0.6875rem] sm:text-xs font-bold tracking-widest text-dgb-500 uppercase mb-2">Status &amp; Roadmap</p>
            <h2 class="text-center text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold mb-8 sm:mb-10 tracking-tight">What's shipped, what's next</h2>

            <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 sm:gap-5">
                @* Shipped — v0 developer preview *@
                <div class="bg-white dark:bg-dgb-900 border border-emerald-200 dark:border-emerald-800/30 rounded-xl p-5 sm:p-6">
                    <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-4">
                        <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-lg bg-emerald-100 dark:bg-emerald-900/30 text-emerald-700 dark:text-emerald-300 flex items-center justify-center shrink-0">
                            <Icon Name="check" Class="w-4 h-4" />
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <div class="text-[0.6875rem] font-bold tracking-widest uppercase text-emerald-700 dark:text-emerald-300">Shipped · v0 preview</div>
                            <div class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">Available today</div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <ul class="space-y-1.5 text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 leading-relaxed m-0 list-disc pl-5">
                        <li>Digi-ID sign-in with 30-day sessions</li>
                        <li>Multi-store dashboard (one account, many shops)</li>
                        <li>BIP84 xpub derivation + single-address modes</li>
                        <li>Hosted checkout with live status (SignalR) + QR + "Open in wallet"</li>
                        <li>Signed webhooks (HMAC-SHA256) with delivery log + one-click replay</li>
                        <li>Per-merchant API keys (create, revoke, show-once secret)</li>
                        <li>Donation button generator — hosted page, JS embed, raw BIP21</li>
                        <li>REST API + OpenAPI docs + 7 KB embed widget</li>
                        <li>Late-payment reconciliation (3-day grace window)</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                @* In progress — v1 public preview *@
                <div class="bg-white dark:bg-dgb-900 border border-amber-200 dark:border-amber-800/40 rounded-xl p-5 sm:p-6">
                    <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-4">
                        <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-lg bg-amber-100 dark:bg-amber-900/30 text-amber-700 dark:text-amber-300 flex items-center justify-center shrink-0">
                            <Icon Name="clock" Class="w-4 h-4" />
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <div class="text-[0.6875rem] font-bold tracking-widest uppercase text-amber-700 dark:text-amber-300">In progress · v1</div>
                            <div class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">Next few weeks</div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <ul class="space-y-1.5 text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 leading-relaxed m-0 list-disc pl-5">
                        <li>Automatic webhook retries with exponential backoff + dead-letter</li>
                        <li>Rate limits + abuse guards on public endpoints</li>
                        <li>Fiat price lock at session creation (USD/EUR/GBP), locked amount enforced at settlement</li>
                        <li>CSV export of sessions + deliveries for bookkeeping</li>
                        <li>Production deployment at <span class="font-mono">pay.dgbwallet.app</span> (Postgres-backed)</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                @* Planned — v2 *@
                <div class="bg-white dark:bg-dgb-900 border border-slate-200 dark:border-dgb-800 rounded-xl p-5 sm:p-6">
                    <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-4">
                        <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-lg bg-dgb-500/10 text-dgb-500 flex items-center justify-center shrink-0">
                            <Icon Name="package" Class="w-4 h-4" />
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <div class="text-[0.6875rem] font-bold tracking-widest uppercase text-dgb-500">Planned · v2</div>
                            <div class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">CMS &amp; SDK reach</div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <ul class="space-y-1.5 text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 leading-relaxed m-0 list-disc pl-5">
                        <li>WooCommerce plugin (PHP)</li>
                        <li>First-party SDKs: Node, .NET, Python</li>
                        <li>Refund helper (generates outgoing-tx URI — non-custodial so you sign it)</li>
                        <li>Per-key scopes (<span class="font-mono">read:sessions</span> vs <span class="font-mono">write:sessions</span>)</li>
                        <li>Invoice-level audit log (who viewed / paid / received the webhook)</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                @* Later — v3 *@
                <div class="bg-white dark:bg-dgb-900 border border-slate-200 dark:border-dgb-800 rounded-xl p-5 sm:p-6">
                    <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-4">
                        <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-lg bg-slate-100 dark:bg-dgb-800 text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 flex items-center justify-center shrink-0">
                            <Icon Name="rocket" Class="w-4 h-4" />
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <div class="text-[0.6875rem] font-bold tracking-widest uppercase text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400">Later · v3+</div>
                            <div class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">Expansion</div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <ul class="space-y-1.5 text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 leading-relaxed m-0 list-disc pl-5">
                        <li>Shopify app</li>
                        <li>POS mode (dedicated tablet checkout)</li>
                        <li>Subscriptions &amp; recurring re-auth</li>
                        <li>Optional custodial settlement layer with fiat on-ramp partner</li>
                        <li>DigiAssets + smart contract payment flows</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

            <p class="text-center text-xs text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 mt-6 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
                DigiPay is open source. Roadmap order can shift based on merchant demand — if something below is blocking you, raise it on the repo and it climbs the list.
            </p>
        </section>

        @* Support card — doubles as a live demo of the donation button widget.
           The <div data-digipay-button> below is replaced by digipay.js at
           mount with the real production-styled button, so visitors literally
           see (and can click) what their own site will look like. *@
        <section class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-10 sm:py-14">
            <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto bg-white dark:bg-dgb-900 border border-slate-200 dark:border-dgb-800 rounded-2xl p-6 sm:p-8 text-center">
                <p class="text-[0.6875rem] sm:text-xs font-bold tracking-widest text-dgb-500 uppercase mb-2">Support the project</p>
                <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-bold mb-3 tracking-tight">Built by humans, runs on DigiByte</h2>
                <p class="text-sm sm:text-base text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 leading-relaxed mb-6 max-w-xl mx-auto">
                    If DigiPay saves you from writing a payment gateway yourself, throw us a few DGB. 100% of donations fund infrastructure and continued development — the button below uses DigiPay itself, so you're also seeing a live demo.
                </p>
                <div class="flex justify-center">
                    <div data-digipay-button
                         data-address="dgb1qvc2d6umstxzrs5xypmvw5wt33mchec4z7ejqaa"
                         data-name="DigiPay"
                         data-label="Thanks for supporting DigiPay!">
                        Tip DGB
                    </div>
                </div>
                <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 mt-4">
                    Or copy the address: <span class="font-mono text-[0.6875rem] break-all">dgb1qvc2d6umstxzrs5xypmvw5wt33mchec4z7ejqaa</span>
                </p>
                <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 mt-2">
                    <a href="/docs#donation-button" class="text-dgb-500 hover:underline">Want one of these on your own site?</a>
                </p>
            </div>
            @* Mount the widget so the placeholder above becomes a real button. *@
            <script src="/embed/digipay.js"></script>
        </section>

        <section class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-10 sm:py-14 text-center">
            <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold mb-6 tracking-tight" data-auth-show="out">Ready?</h2>
            <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold mb-6 tracking-tight" data-auth-show="in">Jump back in</h2>
            <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-3 justify-center">
                <a href="/merchant/signin" data-auth-show="out"
                   class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-6 py-3 bg-dgb-500 hover:bg-dgb-600 text-white font-semibold rounded-xl text-sm sm:text-base no-underline transition-colors">
                    Start accepting DGB
                </a>
                <a href="/merchant" data-auth-show="in"
                   class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-1.5 px-6 py-3 bg-dgb-500 hover:bg-dgb-600 text-white font-semibold rounded-xl text-sm sm:text-base no-underline transition-colors">
                    <Icon Name="dashboard" Class="w-4 h-4" />
                    Open dashboard
                </a>
                <a href="/docs/api"
                   class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-6 py-3 bg-white dark:bg-dgb-900 border border-slate-200 dark:border-dgb-800 text-slate-900 dark:text-white font-semibold rounded-xl text-sm sm:text-base no-underline hover:bg-slate-50 dark:hover:bg-dgb-800 transition-colors">
                    API reference
                </a>
            </div>
            <p class="mt-5 text-xs text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400" data-auth-show="out">
                Need a DigiByte wallet to sign in? Install one at
                <a href="https://dgbwallet.app" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-dgb-500 hover:underline">dgbwallet.app</a>.
            </p>
        </section>
    </main>

    <SiteFooter />
</div>
